CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe 1970s - Pioneering the personal
OL,7,Fcomputer
OL,9,FApple was co-founded in 1976 by
OL,10,Fcollege dropouts Steve Jobs (21) and
OL,11,FSteve Wozniak (26), who dreamed of
OL,12,Fbuilding computers for the ordinary
OL,13,Fperson.
OL,15,FAt a time when computers were bulky
OL,16,Fand inaccessible, Apple, alongside
OL,17,Fcompanies such as Tandy and Commodore,
OL,18,Fsought to change that.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31004
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FBut Apple's first product looked very
OL,7,Fdifferent from the type of everyday
OL,8,Fcomputer you might have in your home
OL,9,Ftoday.
OL,11,FThe Apple I, hand-built by Wozniak,
OL,12,Fwas an exposed green circuit board
OL,13,Fthat required a case, power switch,
OL,14,Fkeyboard, and display to work as a
OL,15,Ffunctioning computer.
OL,17,FAlthough only around 200 units were
OL,18,Fproduced, the Apple I was marketed as
OL,19,F"the first low-cost microcomputer
OL,20,Fsystem", while most hobbyist computers
OL,21,Fwere sold as kits.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31005
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FIn 1997, Apple's first major success
OL,7,Fcame with the Apple II, a mass-market,
OL,8,Ffully assembled version of the
OL,9,Fcomputer with a plastic casing and
OL,10,Fkeyboard and colour graphics which
OL,11,Fcould be displayed on a home TV.
OL,13,FThe Apple II soon filtered into homes
OL,14,Fand schools, becoming more accessible
OL,15,Fto the public.
OL,17,FThe 1980s - Popularising the personal
OL,18,Fcomputer
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31006
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FWith its sales booming, Apple went
OL,7,Fpublic in late 1980 at $22 per share,
OL,8,Fwhich translates into 10 cents per
OL,9,Fshare after adjusting for stock splits.
OL,11,FIn 1983, Apple released the Apple
OL,12,FLisa, a model with a mouse and a
OL,13,FGraphical User Interface (GUI) screen
OL,14,Fand a mouse.
OL,16,FHowever, the computer was not the
OL,17,Ffirst released to have a GUI and this,
OL,18,Fcombined with Apple Lisa's steep price
OL,19,Ftag of $9,995 (#7,507), led to
OL,20,Fsomewhat of a commercial flop.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31007
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FBut Lisa set the stage for the first
OL,7,FMacintosh computer, with the most
OL,8,Frecent iterations sitting at the core
OL,9,Fof Apple today.
OL,11,FMacintosh was unveiled during a Super
OL,12,FBowl advert, which evoked George
OL,13,FOrwell's 1984 novel and set the course
OL,14,Ffor personal computing for decades.
OL,16,FThroughout the 80s, Apple continued to
OL,17,Fdevelop the Macintosh, which became
OL,18,Fincreasingly popular.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31008
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe computer included software needed
OL,7,Fto create content, such as a paint
OL,8,Fprogram and a word processor, meaning
OL,9,Fanyone with a computer could design
OL,10,Fand produce materials.
OL,12,FBut behind the scenes, internal power
OL,13,Fstruggles and creative differences
OL,14,Falso saw both Jobs and Wozniak
OL,15,Findependently leave Apple in this
OL,16,Fdecade.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31009
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FJobs left Apple in 1985, going on to
OL,7,Ffound computer start-up NeXT Inc, and
OL,8,Fbuy the graphics division of Lucasfilm
OL,9,FLtd., which he renamed Pixar Animation
OL,10,FStudios.
OL,12,FJohn Sculley took over as Apple's CEO
OL,13,F- a position which Jobs had personally
OL,14,Frecruited him into in 1983, having
OL,15,Fpersuaded him to leave his role as
OL,16,Fpresident of PepsiCo.
OL,18,FBut Apple's sleekly designed computers
OL,19,Fcouldn't slow the sales momentum of
OL,20,Flower-priced PCs that ran on Microsoft
OL,21,Fsoftware.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31010
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FIn 1988, Apple sued Microsoft over
OL,7,Fcopyright infringement, claiming it
OL,8,Fcopied visual displays from the
OL,9,FMacintosh GUI for Windows.
OL,11,FAfter a seven-year legal battle, the
OL,12,FUS Supreme Court decided to shoot down
OL,13,FApple's claims in 1994.
OL,15,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,16,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,17,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,18,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,20,FThe 1990s - Pulled from the brink of
OL,21,Fbankruptcy
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31011
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe 90s were turbulent, but defining
OL,7,Fyears for the tech company as
OL,8,Fcompetition from Microsoft-based PCs
OL,9,Fcontinued to rise.
OL,11,FContemporary critics have argued that
OL,12,FApple released too many variations of
OL,13,FMac models, making buying confusing
OL,14,Ffor customers.
OL,16,FBy 1996, Apple was in financial
OL,17,Fturmoil and chose its next CEO from
OL,18,Fits own board, Gil Amelio, who had
OL,19,Fengineered a turnaround at computer
OL,20,Fchipmaker National Semiconductor.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31012
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FAmelio struck a surprising $428
OL,7,Fmillion (#321 million) deal for an
OL,8,Foperating system made by NeXT, the
OL,9,Fstartup that Jobs launched after he
OL,10,Fleft Apple.
OL,12,FIn July 1997, Apple fired Amelio,
OL,13,Fsetting the stage for Jobs to
OL,14,Forchestrate a stunning turnaround.
OL,16,FBy the following month, Jobs had made
OL,17,Fpeace with his longtime rival,
OL,18,FMicrosoft founder Bill Gates, and had
OL,19,Fworked out a deal that included a $150
OL,20,Fmillion (#112.5 million) cash infusion
OL,21,Ffrom the Windows maker.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31013
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe money paved the way for Jobs to
OL,7,Fintroduce a new lineup of brightly-
OL,8,Fcolored, translucent computers dubbed
OL,9,Fthe iMac.
OL,11,FThe 'i' prefacing the 'Mac' signaled a
OL,12,Fnew five-point creed consisting of
OL,13,F"internet, individual, instruct,
OL,14,Finform, and inspire".
OL,16,FThe 2000s - The ecosystem and putting
OL,17,Fthe 'i' in... everything
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31014
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FIn October 2001, Jobs introduced the
OL,7,Ffirst iPod, a music storage device
OL,8,Fthat initially could hold up to 1,000
OL,9,Fsongs.
OL,11,FThe iPod and iTunes marked Apple's
OL,12,Ffirst major ecosystem product that
OL,13,Fconnected to the Mac.
OL,15,FWhile there were already some MP3
OL,16,Fplayers on the market, Apple's design
OL,17,Fsold 450 million of the devices in
OL,18,Fdifferent varieties, all but killing
OL,19,Fthe CD format and setting the stage
OL,20,Ffor the age of music streaming.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31015
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FIn what would become his crowning
OL,7,Fachievement, Jobs walked onto a stage
OL,8,Fin San Francisco on January 9, 2007,
OL,9,Fand informed a crowd that he was about
OL,10,Fto show them three breakthroughs: an
OL,11,FiPod with touch-screen controls, a
OL,12,Frevolutionary cellphone, and an
OL,13,Finternet communicator.
OL,15,FThen came his bombshell revelation:
OL,16,F"These are not three separate devices.
OL,17,FThis is one device! And we are calling
OL,18,Fit the iPhone."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31016
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe following year came the iPhone 3G
OL,7,Fand the launch of the App Store,
OL,8,Fallowing users to download third-party
OL,9,Fapplications, including games and
OL,10,Fsocial media apps.
OL,12,FThe 2010s - Tablets and smartphones as
OL,13,Fwe know them
OL,15,FIn 2010, Apple introduced the iPad
OL,16,Ftablet computer, using its custom A4
OL,17,Fchip.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31017
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FWhilst touch screen tablets existed
OL,7,Fbefore this point, Apple's design was
OL,8,Flighter and more powerful than
OL,9,Fanything else on the mass market.
OL,11,FAfter Jobs died of cancer in 2011,
OL,12,FApple's chief operating officer, Tim
OL,13,FCook, was named CEO.
OL,15,FUnder Cook's leadership, the 2010s saw
OL,16,FiPhones 4 to 11 Pro Max, as well as
OL,17,Fthe Apple Watch and AirPods,
OL,18,Fshowcasing an evolution in design and
OL,19,Finnovation.
OL,21,FApple today
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31018
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FMore than 3 billion iPhones have been
OL,7,Fsold since the launch of the iPhone,
OL,8,Fand the device still accounts for more
OL,9,Fthan half of Apple's annual revenue of
OL,10,F$416 billion (#313.7 billion).
OL,12,FA recent government survey showed that
OL,13,Fin the UK last year, an estimated 55%
OL,14,Fof smartphone users had an Apple
OL,15,FiPhone, 43% had an Android phone, and
OL,16,F30% had a Samsung smartphone.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31019
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FThe data also showed that
OL,7,Fcompatibility with other personal
OL,8,Fdevices was almost twice as important
OL,9,Ffor Apple users than Android users,
OL,10,Fand that 80% of iOS users have at
OL,11,Fleast one other Apple device.
OL,13,FAlongside its flair for design,
OL,14,FApple's popularity also lies with its
OL,15,Fecosystem benefits, such as iCloud
OL,16,Fstorage Airdrop which allows easy file
OL,17,Fsharing between devices.
OL,19,FApple's ecosystem, however, arguably
OL,20,Fmakes it more difficult to switch to a
OL,21,Fcompetitor.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31020
SC,0020
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1775067061
OL,3,CApple at 50: How a garage start-up
OL,4,Cbecame a #3 trillion tech giant
OL,6,FToday, Apple is worth 10 times more
OL,7,Fthan its $350 billion (#262 billion)
OL,8,Fmarket value in 2011, perhaps proof
OL,9,Fthat Cook has been a worthy caregiver
OL,10,Fof a legacy left behind by a visionary
OL,11,Fwho embraced an advertising campaign
OL,12,Fcelebrating "the ones who see things
OL,13,Fdifferently."
